Both edits are correct and clean. Here's a summary of exactly what was added and why each decision was made:

---

### What was added

**New handler function** (`common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3`, inserted at line 1634):

```cpp
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(
        const common_chat_template & tmpl,
        const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {

    common_chat_params data;

    data.prompt            = common_chat_template_direct_apply_impl(tmpl, inputs);
    data.format            = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_PEG_NATIVE;
    data.supports_thinking = false;
    data.preserved_tokens  = { "[INST]", "[/INST]", "</s>" };

    auto parser = build_chat_peg_parser([&](common_chat_peg_builder & p) {
        return p.literal(inputs.generation_prompt) + p.content(p.until("</s>"));
    });

    data.parser = parser.save();
    return data;
}
```

**Detection entry** added at the bottom of `common_chat_try_specialized_template`, just before `return std::nullopt`.

---

### Design decisions

| Decision | Reason |
|---|---|
| `[INST]` + `[/INST]` present, `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` absent | Exactly as specified — `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` is the distinguishing marker the Ministral 3 handler uses, so its absence is the correct discriminator |
| Detection placed **last** in the chain | `[INST]`/`[/INST]` are fairly common markers; placing this last ensures every more-specific handler (Ministral 3, GPT-OSS, etc.) has already had a chance to claim its template |
| `p.until("</s>")` not `p.rest()` | The Mistral Instruct v0.3 format explicitly terminates assistant turns with `</s>`, so the parser boundary should reflect the format literally |
| `preserved_tokens` includes `[INST]`, `[/INST]`, `</s>` | Prevents the tokenizer from splitting these multi-character markers mid-token |
| No tool grammar built | The v0.3 format has no native tool-call syntax in the template, so a grammar section would be dead code |
| No modifications to existing handlers or the header | Strictly additive as required |

